{"answer": "The evidence suggests fine-tuning overtakes few-shot performance on domain-specific tasks regardless of scale — fine-tuned 7B models match or exceed 175B few-shot performance. LoRA makes fine-tuning practical with 10-100x fewer parameters. RAG shifts the threshold further by reducing hallucination to under 5%, meaning smaller fine-tuned models with retrieval can match larger few-shot models. The crossover likely occurs at tasks requiring specialized vocabulary and structured reasoning."}